commit 896891213b1d6c64983371da722277f4f9be3d03
Author: Uladzislau Rezki (Sony) <urezki@gmail.com>

mm/vmalloc: Use dedicated unbound workqueue for vmap purge/drain

This commit introduces a dedicated WQ_UNBOUND workqueue for vmap
purging and draining to prevent watchdog warnings on systems with high
CPU counts. It uses WQ_MEM_RECLAIM to ensure forward progress under
memory pressure.

Link: https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260319074307.2325-1-lirongqing@baidu.com/

> diff --git a/mm/vmalloc.c b/mm/vmalloc.c
> --- a/mm/vmalloc.c
> +++ b/mm/vmalloc.c
[ ... ]
> @@ -2385,29 +2392,30 @@ static bool __purge_vmap_area_lazy(unsigned long start, unsigned long end,
>  		nr_purge_helpers = atomic_long_read(&vmap_lazy_nr) / lazy_max_pages();
>  		nr_purge_helpers = clamp(nr_purge_helpers, 1U, nr_purge_nodes) - 1;
>  
> +		for_each_vmap_node(vn) {
> +			vn->work_queued = false;
> +
> +			if (list_empty(&vn->purge_list))
> +				continue;
>  
>  			if (nr_purge_helpers > 0) {
>  				INIT_WORK(&vn->purge_work, purge_vmap_node);
> +				vn->work_queued = schedule_drain_vmap_work(&vn->purge_work);
[ ... ]
> +		/* Wait for completion if queued any. */
> +		for_each_vmap_node(vn) {
> +			if (vn->work_queued) {
>  				flush_work(&vn->purge_work);
>  				nr_purged_areas += vn->nr_purged;
>  			}
>  		}

Could this lead to a workqueue rescuer deadlock under memory pressure?

Since schedule_drain_vmap_work() queues vn->purge_work to drain_vmap_wq,
and drain_vmap_work (the caller of this function) is also running on
drain_vmap_wq, we have a parent work item waiting on child work items
queued to the same workqueue.

> @@ -5483,3 +5491,15 @@ void __init vmalloc_init(void)
>  	vmap_node_shrinker->scan_objects = vmap_node_shrink_scan;
>  	shrinker_register(vmap_node_shrinker);
>  }
> +
> +static int __init vmalloc_init_workqueue(void)
> +{
> +	struct workqueue_struct *wq;
> +
> +	wq = alloc_workqueue("vmap_drain", WQ_UNBOUND | WQ_MEM_RECLAIM, 0);

If the system is under severe memory pressure and cannot allocate normal
worker threads, the WQ_MEM_RECLAIM rescuer thread will begin executing
drain_vmap_work.

When the rescuer thread reaches the flush_work() call above, it will block
waiting for vn->purge_work to complete. Because the single rescuer thread
is now blocked, it cannot pick up and execute the child works it just
queued, creating a permanent deadlock.

